Peak 301® — science‑driven rejuvenation

What it does

Plant‑based formulation designed to help aging asphalt shingles regain flexibility and granule retention, supporting UV and weather resistance when replacement can wait.

  • Single‑day application on eligible roofs
  • Adds years of useful life (roof‑condition dependent)
  • Eco‑considerate and applied by trained crews

Always assess condition, ventilation, and any prior coatings before approval.

Popular add‑ons
  • Roof wash / algae removal
  • Minor tune‑ups (nail pops, small repairs)
  • Photo set + maintenance summary

Revenue‑Share Economics

Simple, transparent math so you can price confidently and protect your margin.

How it works

  • You sell Peak 301® under your brand; we fulfill as your white‑label applicator.
  • Per‑square base covers materials, labor, and application.
  • You keep everything over the base price as your margin.
  • Optional add‑ons (roof wash, photo/report bundle, tune‑ups) increase ticket size.

Ask about current Metro Atlanta & North GA base rates and territory availability.

Peak 301® vs Roof Maxx® — at a glance

Both are plant‑based rejuvenators for aging asphalt shingles. Program structures and terms differ by brand—verify details with each provider.

FeaturePeak 301Roof Maxx
TechnologyPlant‑based oils formulated for flexibility & granule retention.Plant‑based soy oils marketed to restore flexibility & weathering.
Typical programPartner/applicator model supporting contractor independence.Branded dealer network under Roof Maxx identity.
PositioningAlternative when a roof still has service life left; maintenance‑friendly.Alternative to delay replacement; marketed savings vs replacement.

Third‑party marks are property of their owners. This summary is informational only—always confirm eligibility and written terms per project.

Partner FAQs

Who is a good fit?

Roofing and exterior‑cleaning companies with steady homeowner traffic and interest in a maintenance‑first offer.

Turnaround time?

Most eligible roofs are completed in a single day; scheduling varies by volume and weather.

What do we provide?

Sales enablement, measurements help, white‑label application, photos, and a maintenance summary.

Do we need training?

We onboard you on estimating, eligibility, and homeowner education. No new crew required on your side.

Is every roof eligible?

No. Age, condition, ventilation, and prior coatings determine eligibility. We verify each job first.

Service area?

Metro Atlanta & North Georgia; ZIP‑based priorities apply. Ask about your coverage.
